SENATE RESOLUTION 298
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Officer Jim Dandy
upon being named Haywood County
Correctional Officer of the Year.
WHEREAS, the Volunteer State is especially proud to be the home of so many valiant
men and women who continue the time-honored tradition of public service in law enforcement,
dedicating their time and efforts to aiding those in emergency situations and apprehending
those who have broken the law; and
WHEREAS, Officer Jim Dandy of the Baxter Police Department is one such courageous
public servant, who was recently named Haywood County Correctional Officer of the Year by
Sheriff Billy Garrett, Jr.; and
WHEREAS, Officer Jim Dandy has contributed greatly to the safety of the citizens of
Haywood County, serving with tremendous courage, fortitude, and professionalism and making
a significant impact for the betterment of his community; and
WHEREAS, Officer Dandy epitomizes the spirit and commitment that are characteristic
of a true Tennessean, and his professionalism and dedication to Haywood County are evident
to all who know him; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Officer Jim Dandy for his
dedication to the State of Tennessee and its citizens; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and congratulate Jim
Dandy upon being named Haywood County Correctional Officer of the Year, thank him for his
meritorious service to the citizens of Haywood County and the State of Tennessee, and extend
to him our best wishes for every future success.
